`Iterator` of `synchronizedList` is not (and can&#39;t be) synchronized, you need to synchronize on the list manually while iterating (see [javadoc][1]):

    synchronized(arrayList) {
        Iterator it=arrayList.iterator(); 
        while(it.hasNext()) { 
            System.out.println(it.next()); 
       } 
    }

Another approach is to use a [`CopyOnWriteArrayList`][2] instead of `Collections.synchronizedList()`. It implements a copy-on-write semantic and therefore doesn&#39;t require synchronization.


  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Collections.html#synchronizedList-java.util.List-
  [2]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/CopyOnWriteArrayList.html

