Start by learning and following the Java coding standards.  Your class names should begin with a capital letter: `Apple.java` and `Mango.java`.  It&#39;ll make your code readable by other Java developers.

As for access, either class just has to obtain an instance of the class it wants:

    package fruit;
    
    public class Apple {
